# Exemple implementation of the Gateway Communication Module.
In this part, you will have to implement Gateway Communication code.
There are two parts, hence two handlers
 1. Generic Query - to GET the value
 2. Generic Command - absolute SET and realtive SET value (increase/decrease)

## Generic Query
This handler is called when the Snips application needs to get the current value of a device (temperature, brightness, shutters position, sensors etc)
It receives an array of commands & UID of the devices as input. 
The command name is as well as the UID are defined by **you** in the GGDF.

Sample input to receive (type Object):
`[
   {
      "name":"CurrentState",
      "uid":"knxcom_function_20190812133320520"
   },
   {
      "name":"CurrentBrightness",
      "uid":"knxcom_function_20190902090905369"
   }
]`

This input is a list of object query from the description list you provided. 

If the Gateway communication module uses a Web API (http), you can re-use the sample flow. You will need to adapt the
by changing SET node. Else, you have to replace all the nodes between two links in the handler.
If you intend to keep the flow, you can make a copy and detach it from the flow.


Before sending out the response from the gateway server to the link out of generic query, you should put it 
in a Object format that can be read by realKNX.

Sample output to send (type Object):
`[{
        "Data": [{
                "Value": "OFF",
                "uid": "knxcom_function_20190812133320520"
            }
        ],
        "Result": true
    }, {
        "Data": [{
                "Value": 46.3,
                "uid": "knxcom_function_20190902090905369"
            }
        ],
        "Result": true
    }
]`

# Generic command
This handler is called to get the current value of the device (on,off,decrease,set etc)
The link in node of the generic command is also connected to Snips application. It receive 
commands of devices as input. It could be one command or an array of commands at a time.
Sample input to receive (type Object):
`[
   {
      "name":"On",
      "uid":"knxcom_function_20190812133320520",
      "value":"ON"
   },
   {
      "name":"On",
      "uid":"knxcom_function_20190902090905369",
      "value":100
   }
]
`
This input is a list of object command from the description list you provided. 

Before send out the response from the gateway server to the link out of generic query, you should put it 
in a Object format that can be read by realknx.
Sample output to send (type Object):
`[
   {
      "Result":true
   },
   {
      "Result":false
   }
]`
true is when the server repond correctly, otherwise, Result is false
